OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFrance to pay 38m citizens 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F100 euros each to ease     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcosts                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The French government has announced a  
OL,6, one-off payment of 100 euros (#84;     
OL,7, $116) for each citizen whose monthly   
OL,8, net income is 2,000 euros or less, to  
OL,9, help counter the surge in fuel and     
OL,10, energy prices.                         
OL,12,FThe "inflation allowance" will go to   
OL,13,Fabout 38 million French people         
OL,14,Fautomatically, including those who do  
OL,15,Fnot drive a car or ride a motorbike.   
OL,17,FThe first payments will go to business 
OL,18,Femployees in late December.            
OL,20,FCivil servants, students and pensioners
OL,21,Fwill get theirs in early 2022.         
